SIMPLE: pleasantry
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pleasantry
<hw>Pleas"ant*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Pleasantries</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F.
<ets>plaisanterie</ets>. See <er>Pleasant</er>.]</ety> <def>That which
denotes or promotes pleasure or good humor; cheerfulness; gayety;
merriment; especially, an agreeable playfulness in conversation; a
jocose or humorous remark; badinage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The grave abound in <qex>pleasantries</qex>, the dull in repartees
and points of wit.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The keen observation and ironical <qex>pleasantry</qex> of a
finished man of the world.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pleasant-tongued</ent>⟦br⟧
